# Implementation Standards for PR Cards

**Precise values from GitHub's Primer design system.**

## PR State Badge Pattern

```css
.pr-state-badge {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 4px;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 2em;  /* pill shape */
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  line-height: 18px;
}

/* Open */
.pr-state-badge.open {
  color: #ffffff;
  background-color: #238636;
}

/* Draft */
.pr-state-badge.draft {
  color: #ffffff;
  background-color: #6e7681;
}

/* Closed */
.pr-state-badge.closed {
  color: #ffffff;
  background-color: #cf222e;
}

/* Merged */
.pr-state-badge.merged {
  color: #ffffff;
  background-color: #8957e5;
}
```

## Typography Scale

- **PR title:** `font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #24292f`
- **PR number + meta:** `font-size: 0.75rem; color: #57606a`
- **Branch names:** `font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; background: rgba(175, 184, 193, 0.2); padding: 0.1em 0.3em; border-radius: 3px`

## Card Border System

- Border: `1px solid #d0d7de`
- Border radius: `0.375rem` (6px)
- Row separator: `1px solid #e1e4e8`
- No shadow on default state — shadow only on `.card:hover`: `0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.12)`

## Icon Sizes

- PR state icon: `16x16px` inside badge
- Review avatar: `20x20px` circle
- CI check icon: `16x16px`
- Label dot: `8x8px` circle using label color
